laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis, decreased liver attenuation consistent with fatty infiltration, enlarged appendix measuring up to 1.2 cm in diameter with hyper-enhancing walls and significant surrounding fat stranding, free fluid in the cul-de-sac, no organized abscess collection, no focal liver lesions, normal gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, bladder, and terminal ureters.
